    category: "Data Processing",
    difficulty: "intermediate",
    tags: ["memory", "pool", "allocator", "block", "arena", "allocation", "free"],
    description: "Implements a bump/arena-style memory pool allocator for SWMM5. Pre-allocates large blocks of memory and serves allocation requests by advancing an offset pointer within the current block. When a block is exhausted, a new block is allocated. Supports pool reset for bulk deallocation. This pattern reduces fragmentation and speeds up allocation for SWMM5's many small objects.",
    equations: "offset += size (bump); newBlock when offset + size > blockSize",
    inputs: "Block size, requested allocation size",
